\n{{India-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian Hindi-language crime television series}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Savdhaan India\n| image                    = Savdhaan_India-serial.jpg\n| caption                  = <!--Don't use captions for obvious title cards, please follow the [[MOS:TV]].-->\n| show_name_2              = Savdhan India \u2013 Darr Kar Nahi Datt Kar <br> Crime Alert\n| genre                    = Crime\n| creator                  = Ajit Thakur <br> Amar Deb <br> [[Anirban Bhattacharyya]]\n| writer                   = Rajesh Beri <br> Aayush Agrawal <br> Manish Shrivastava <br> Amitava Mitra <br> [[Anirban Bhattacharyya]]\n| director                 = Ajay Veermal\n| creative_director        = Prince Duggal <br> Aayush Agrawal <br> [[Nitin Dwivedi]]\n| starring                 = [[Sushant Singh]]<br>[[Gaurav Chopra]]<br>[[Mohnish Behl]]<br>[[Pooja Gaur]]<br>[[Hiten Tejwani]]<br>[[Sidharth Shukla]]<br>[[Divya Dutta]]<br>[[Saurabh Raj Jain]]<br>[[Sakshi Tanwar]]<br>[[Karmveer Choudhary]]<br>[[Sanjay Gagnani]]\n| country                  = [[India]]\n| language                 = [[Hindi]]\n| num_seasons              = 3\n| num_episodes             = 2,942 <!-- as of 19 October 2019 --><!-- Do not uncomment the preceding text. This field is for a number only and the date should not be visible. -->\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n*RowdyRascal <ref name=PH/>\n*[[Endemol]] India<ref name=PH/>\n*Keylight Production<ref name=PH/>\n*Saregama India Ltd<ref name=PH/>\n*Franklin Pictures Pvt. Ltd<ref name=PH/>\n*Jagannath Entertainment<ref name=PH/>\n*Baba Arts<ref name=PH/>\n*Flying Turtle<ref name=PH/>\n*[[Director's Kut Productions]]<ref name=PH>{{cite web| title = Savdhan India gets a new tagline; chops few production houses | url = http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/savdhan-india-gets-new-tagline-chops-few-production-housesread-more |date=15 November 2013| accessdate = 8 May 2017| publisher = Tellychakkar}}</ref>\n}}\n| cinematography           = Indranil Singha, Naren Gedia, Shakil B. Khan, Sanjeev Mohapatra\n| editor                   = \n| runtime                  = 50 minutes\n| network                  = [[Life OK]] (2012\u201317)<br><nowiki>Star Bharat (2017-present)</nowiki>\n| picture_format           = {{ubl|[[576i]]|[[1080i]] (HDTV)}}\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|df=y|2012|04|23}}\n| last_aired               = Present\n| website                  = http://www.hotstar.com/tv/savdhaan-india-darr-kar-nahin-dat-kar/15034\n| website_title            = Hotstar\n}}\n\n'''''Savdhaan India \u2013 India Fights Back''''' (English: ''Attention India! \u2013 India Fights Back'') is an Indian Hindi-language crime show aired by [[Star Bharat]]. The series is hosted by [[Ashutosh Rana]], [[Tisca Chopra]], [[Sushant Singh]], [[Gaurav Chopra]], [[Mohnish Behl]], [[Pooja Gaur]], [[Saurabh Raj Jain]], [[Shivani Tomar]], [[Pratyusha Banerjee]], [[Hiten Tejwani]], [[Divya Dutta]] and [[Siddharth Shukla]]. It focuses on real-life crime incidents in India and the story of struggle of the victims in order to get justice for their sufferings.<ref>{{cite web| title = Rushad Rana &amp; Falaq Naaz in Savdhaan India | url = http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-07/tv/38345786_1_india-fights-savdhaan-india-savdhan-india |date=7 April 2013|accessdate = 7 January 2014 | work = The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title = Akhlaque Khan &amp; Pooja Sharma in Savdhaan India!| url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news-interviews/Akhlaque-Khan-Pooja-Sharma-in-Savdhaan-India/articleshow/24477596.cms? |date=21 October 2013| accessdate = 7 January 2014| work = The Times of India|quote=Life OK's 'Savdhaan India-India Fights Back', never fails to impress the viewers with its gripping real life crime based stories.}}</ref>\n\nInitially the series aired as ''Crime Alert'' on Life OK.<ref>{{cite web | title = Savdhaan India \u2013 India Fights back |publisher= STAR Player \n| url = http://www.hotstar.com/tv/savdhaan-india/363| accessdate = 16 November 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513001642/http://www.hotstar.com/tv/savdhaan-india/363|archivedate=13 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> A rebooted version of the series called ''Savdhaan India \u2013 India Fights Back'' began broadcast on Life OK on 23 July 2012.{{citation needed|date=November 2016}} Versions of the program (focusing on a particular Indian state/city) have also aired as Savdhaan India \u2013 Maharashtra Fights Back, hosted by [[Shreyas Talpade]], ''Savdhaan India \u2013 Mumbai Fights Back'', hosted by [[Atul Kulkarni (actor born 1965)|Atul Kulkarni]]<ref>{{cite web | title = Atul Kulkarni is happy to be associated with 'Savdhaan India' | url = http://ibnlive.in.com/news/atul-kulkarni-is-happy-to-be-associated-with-savdhaan-india/412455-44-124.html |publisher=CNN-IBN|date=7 August 2013| accessdate = 7 January 2014 }}</ref> ''Savdhaan India \u2013 Punjab Fights Back'' and ''Savdhaan India \u2013 U.P Fights Back''. The show continue to air on Replacement Channel of Life OK which is [[STAR Bharat]] from 28 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://newsnexa.com/news/star-india-star-bharat-channel/|title=Star India to launch a new Star Bharat Channel on 28 August 2017\n|publisher=News Nexa|date=27 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe show is one of the [[List of longest-running Indian television series|longest-running Indian television series]] based on episode count.{{Citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n\n==Series overview==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Season !!Episodes !!Season Premiere !!Season Ending !! Channel !! Host(s) !! Ref\n|-\n|Savdhaan India - India fights back\n| 2354\n| 23 April 2012\n| 27 August 2017\n| [[Life OK]]\n| [[Sushant Singh]], [[Sakshi Tanwar]],<br/>[[Mohnish Behl]], [[Pooja Gor]],<br/>[[Gaurav Chopra]], [[Hiten Tejwani]], <br/>[[Siddharth Shukla]], [[Divya Dutta]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotstar.com/tv/savdhaan-india/363|title=Watch Savdhaan India on hotstar.com |date=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|Savdhaan India: Darr Kar Nahin Dat Kar\n| 193\n| 28 August 2017\n| 23 March 2018\n| [[Star Bharat]]\n| [[Sushant Singh]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotstar.com/tv/savdhaan-india-darr-kar-nahin-dat-kar/15034|title=Watch Savdhaan India Darr Kar Nahin Dat Kar on hotstar.com |date=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|Savdhaan India: Waqt Ke Saath Apraadhi Hua upgrade, Aap Bhi ho Jaayiye up to date\n|360 (as of 7 September 2019)\n| 18 July 2018\n|Present\n| [[Star Bharat]]\n| [[Sushant Singh]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.televisionpost.com/star-bharat-to-air-new-season-of-savdhaan-india-from-18-july/|title=Star Bharat to air new season of 'Savdhaan India' from 18 July - TelevisionPost: Latest News, India's Television, Cable, DTH, TRAI|date=4 July 2018|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizasialive.com/star-bharat-bring-back-savdhaan-india-month/|title=Star Bharat to bring back 'Savdhaan India' this month|first=Raj|last=Baddhan|date=4 July 2018|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Controversy==\nThe show has landed in controversy on numerous occasions where it has been seen as a bad influence by its sensational portrayal of crime.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/buzz/news-inspired-by-tv-show-savdhaan-india-11-year-old-girl-files-rape-case-against-her-father-427975|title=Inspired by TV show 'Savdhaan India', 11-year-old girl files rape case against her father|first=Aakriti|last=Ganguli|date=15 February 2018|website=www.indiatvnews.com|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref> In February 2018 in Delhi, a man residing in [[New Friends Colony]] was accused of rape by his 11-year-old daughter.<ref name=contr/> The 11-year-old girl later admitted in court, said that she complained against her father after watching Savdhaan India and that she \"exaggerated things\" before her mother and the police.<ref name=contr/> She said that the show gave her the impression that her father's innocent kisses were something \u2018wrong\u2019.<ref name=contr/> Her father was acquitted by the court.<ref name=contr>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/bad-influence-girl-charged-father-with-rape-after-watching-savdhaan-india-court-acquits-dad/1066972/|title=Bad influence? Girl charged father with rape after watching Savdhaan India, court acquits dad|date=15 February 2018|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Episodic cast==\n* [[Mamik Singh]] as Naveen Neelam (Episode 611) / Bhanu Uday Singh (Episode 664)\n* [[Maninder Singh (actor) | Maninder Singh]] as Inspector (Episode 458)\n* [[Salil Ankola]] as Kunal Singh (Episode 267)\n* [[Ulka Gupta]] as Megha Singh (Episode 267) / Alka (Episode 916)\n* [[Mala Salariya]] as RJ Rohini (Episode 1269) / Reshma (Episode 2230)\n* [[Prachi Thakker]] as Rukmani (Episode 1472) / Jignesh's Wife (Episode 2272)\n* [[Sara Khan (TV actress) | Sara Khan]] as Savitri (Episode 766)\n* [[Parul Chauhan]] as Roopa (Episode 47)\n* Ashish Dixit as Rajan / Varun / Satinder Singh\n* [[Sonia Singh]] as Aparna (Episode 1982)\n* Niyati Joshi as Priya (Episode 516) / Parmeet (Episode 639) / Mehak (Episode 1244) / Dipika (Episode 1311) / Esha (Episode 1451) / Mahika (Episode 1528) / Neeru (Episode 1664) / Neeraj's Second Wife (Episode 2190)\n* [[Gunn Kansara]] as Geeta (Episode 1657) / Amrita (Episode 1789)\n* [[Namrata Thapa]] as Maya Sameer Malhotra (Episode 704) / Neeta (Episode 1132) / Mausami (Episode 1316)\n* [[Anushka Singh]] as Amandeep Kaur (Episode 65 & Episode 66) / Uma Devi (Episode 41) / Archana Arvind Gupta (Episode 182) / Suman (Episode 763) / Shraddha Sharma (Episode 1352) / Manisha (Episode 1561) / Shilpi (Episode 1628) / Amit's wife (Episode 1694) / Dr. Madhu (Episode 1776)\n* Preeti Gandwani as Shweta (Episode 1308) / Kiran's Sister-In-Law (Episode 1506) / Sheetal (Episode 162